<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Martial" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Martial,</orth> 1) pertaining to war, opposed to civil: <cit><quote>m. law,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 46</bibl></cit>. <emph>a m. man</emph> == a warrior, <bibl n="shak. luc 200" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 74</bibl>. <cit><quote>arts and m. exercises,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 74</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) warlike, becoming or like a true warrior: <cit><quote>a m. outside,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.122" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 122</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>write it in a m. hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a maid, and be so m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>warlike and m. Talbot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with a m. scorn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 166</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with m. stalk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 66</bibl></cit>.

<lb />3) resembling Mars: <cit><quote>his foot Mercurial, his M. thigh,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.310" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 310</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="697" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>